Fine Finishes Design Inc. is a premier design and decorating firm serving the Greater Toronto area since 1997. 

We have a well earned reputation for attention to detail and professionalism in residential and commercial design.  Fine Finishes Design Inc. works closely with their clients and places special emphasis on understanding their unique needs, tastes and budget.  
Andrea Colman, the Principal Designer and Creative Director of Fine Finishes Design Inc. oversees each project personally ensuring the highest quality service.

Andrea graduated with the highest honours in the CIDC Design Program and is considered to be one of the best designers in the greater Toronto area.

Andrea is one of the founding members of The Benjamin Moore Painting and Decorating Services in North America and has sat on the Advisory Council for Benjamin Moore’s Painting and Decorating Services Canada.

profile:
We are pleased to offer you our qualified assistance in your Building Permit and architectural design needs. We are fully insured and registered with the Ontario Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing that outlined Ontario Building Code. We have years of experience behind us when it comes to building permits.
Our simple yet effective approach

    * Our team will visit your property and carry out necessary detailed measurements.
    * Based on the measurements and other information, we file all necessary drawings and other paperwork on your behalf.
    * We will submit the drawings to the city.
    * We will ensure the design changes are reflected to provide correct information and get your permit as soon as possible

we have successfully completed over 400 building permits.

Creative Interiors is a Toronto based design firm, specializing in custom decorating for residential & commercial clients.

Roz Pages’ background derives from the UK, once based in London, one of the top cities in the world for design. Having spent many working holidays in Europe, France & Italy being her favorite, she brings to Toronto a European flair which comes from her passion for fabrics & color. She is dedicated to creating exceptional, distinctive & uniquely personal Interiors.

Roz works with Realtors and has just staged a 5 Million Dollar house located by the Cricket Club. 

Services include:  Interior Decorating, Staging, Project Management and Colour Consultation.
All hired contractors are licensed and insured.

profile:
Based in Toronto, AV Style specializes in transforming residential and commercial spaces using PVC stretch ceiling technology, printed wall coverings, integrated lighting and more. Our reputation for quality has helped us build strong relationships with trade professionals and dealers across Canada. 

AV Style was born from a desire to provide beautiful and affordable alternatives to traditional finishes like drywall, stucco and popcorn ceilings. The key to our success is our strong, creative and highly skilled team of craftsmen experienced in all aspects of stretch ceilings and wall coverings — from design and consultation to installation and repair. 

From day one we’ve taken a collaborative approach that honors the vision of our clients and partners. We are proud to have our work on display in homes and commercial spaces throughout North America, Europe, and the Middle East.

Hi, My name is Barbara. I'm thrilled to announce that I'm celebrating 18 years of Decorating & Designing.

Barbara Nyke Interiors & Design is a residential interior design & decorating studio.  We design custom kitchens, baths and décor for busy professionals primarily in: Toronto, North York, Etobicoke, Mississauga, Caledon, Vaughan, Richmond Hill, The Beach and Scarborough.  For projects located elsewhere, we are delighted to take our designs beyond the GTA.

Here's an article about "Why You Need to Hire a Kitchen Designer" - I'm the featured kitchen designer in the article.. Please copy & paste: https://blog.homestars.com/expert-opinion-why-need-kitchen-designer/

To get your project started, book a 2-hr kitchen design consultation with me.  I'll give you a comprehensive set of preliminary design recommendations including space planning, how to maximize counter space, cabinetry design, estimated project costs and more. Then we're ready for Step 2 of the NIKKA DESIGN process.

profile:
Yorkville Design Centre has been an exclusive Downsview Kitchens retailer since it was established in 1972.  Known throughout the world for its fine craftsmanship, attention to detail and lasting value, YDC specifies Downsview Kitchens.

From our Toronto showroom in Yorkville Village, the team at Yorkville Design Centre assists you with your design needs as a designer of kitchens, bathrooms, wardrobes, media rooms and more, including space planning and architecture. Depending on your specific needs using Downsview Kitchens cabinetry, our team at YDC is able to custom design for you. 

Design Process 
We book a consultation with you to go over your space planning needs in either a new build or renovation and then measure and draw up conceptual ideas for your new space in 3D. We bring the ideas into CAD and prepare accurate quotes for our Downsview Kitchens cabinets based on our consultation with you and the design we create. You can engage additional services from Yorkville Design Centre when you purchase your cabinets from us. Then we also provide you with interior design services to finish the space including shopping for the right products and periodically reviewing completion of the envisioned design. 

Products 
Downsview Kitchens cabinetry, countertops, backsplashes, hardware, lighting, plumbing fixtures, appliances, wall coverings, windows, flooring, trim details, molding details.

profile:
XEEN DESIGNS is a full-service interior design studio based in Milton, Ontario, servicing Greater Toronto Area and other areas including Burlington, Oakville, Niagara, Guelph, Kitchener, Waterloo, and more.
We make interior spaces functional, safe, and beautiful for almost every type of building. Our team creates indoor spaces functional, safe, and beautiful by determining space requirements and selecting essential and decorative items, such as colors, lighting, and materials. We are dedicated to making clients happy and satisfied by listening to their needs and collaborating with their ideas to offer multiple solutions for your design problems.
services:
1. Full-Service Interior Design - We will assist in all aspects of a project from start to finish – including consulting with architects and builders and providing a tailored approach to finishes and décor right through to final touches. We offer each of our clients a unique and innovative solution to their design needs. You won’t have to lift a finger. We’ll take care of everything, from budget management to final installations.

2. Interior Design Consultation - Every project starts with a design consult, however big or small. After we make that brief chat and introduce each other, it's time to determine the real goal of the project. Whether you are on a tight budget or simply just looking for some design ideas and want to pick our brains, this 90 mins session will get you on the right path. During our time together, we will discuss what you love or don’t about your home, current design trends, which is the best one for your space, and what are your goals

3. Home Staging - If you’re putting your home on the market, you want to make sure that you’re getting the best return on your investment. We help create stunning home stylings that wow real estate buyers as soon as they walk up to your front door. From fully furnishing vacant homes to display suites, in our capable hands, your home becomes a showpiece designed specifically to appeal to the greatest number of buyers.

4. Space Planning - Have an unconventional space or just have no time? Need some ideas to spruce up a small area or a part of your house, or just an office space - this service is just for you then! Get all you want packaged roomwise!  

5. Designer for the day - The Designer for a Day service is ideal for those who want professional advice and guidance without a long-term commitment.   This unique 4-hour, one-on-one intensive consultation gives you direct access to professional design expertise.

6. Designer on call (Virtual) - 
This is a ONE HOUR virtual design consult session. Bring in all your questions during the virtual meeting, we can discuss them all. After our session, I will send you an email with suggestions on design and decoration.

profile:
WELCOME TO LOVELIGHT™ HOME DESIGN


We shine in creating calm, gorgeous spaces that not only create a lasting impression but are also beautifully functional.

Perhaps your space may be negatively impacting your sleep, work, money, relationships, safety, or convenience?

Or are you ready to refresh or upgrade your space to move forward with your life?

We enhance your home living experience and improve your quality of life with home wellness design.


Tasia's intuitive home wellness designs are relationship-based, taking into account her observations and perceptions regarding each member of the household’s relationship with the space as well as each of their relationships with each other. With her holistic insights and the use of the insightful Home Harmony Healing™ Advantage, Tasia creates simple, peaceful designs that flow with how you and your family need and want to use the space, taking into account the needs and health of the family at all levels. 

Tasia’s holistic approach transforms the space so that you feel nourished, at peace, and naturally in tune with the energy around you, while meeting the wellness of the entire household at all levels: mental, physical, emotional, medical, social, and environmental and more. 

She will strive tirelessly to make your space everything that you need it to be and far more than you expected or ever thought possible. Drawing on her wide expertise from art to science, Tasia works within your budget, schedule, comfort level, empowering you with choices, tools, strategies and support to create a peaceful, joyful, loving home.

An expert in Feng Shui, Interior Design and Design for Disability Access, Tasia is also an Intervenor for Deafblind Individuals. Trained in both physical and intellectual disability access, she believes that respecting an individual's access to their space is crucial. Her experience interpreting visual and auditory information for her clients enables her to see the world from a compassionate perspective. Using Environmental Psychology, she looks at the sensory impact your surroundings have on your health. She believes wholeheartedly in supporting each person, with honesty and love, according to their unique differences and circumstances. Which is also why she loves designing for the neurodivergent, for accessibility and for seniors.


OUR SIGNATURE DESIGN SERVICES

1) Ready to Build, Remodels and Renovations Design Service
From providing necessary construction drawings, floor plans, material selections and project management, we strive to create a unique vision that we execute with the utmost attention to detail and design expertise.

2) Room Renewals or Art, Decor and Furnishing Design Service
Our Room Renewal package is a high-end decorating service created to reawaken spaces in need of a design lift. With a design concept in mind and thoughtful space planning, we can create an optimal floor plan layout for your space.

3) Home Office or Wellness Studio Design Consultation
We integrate holistic design elements, environmental psychology and healthcare to promote balance and harmony in your home office or a wellness studio. 


To find out more about whether our services can complement your needs and desires, please contact us here. Or you can visit our website and book a complimentary discovery call so that we can chat. 

I look forward to speaking with you to see if I can support you in completely transforming your space toward wellness for your body, mind and spirit.

Tasia Keeng
Director & Home Wellness Designer
Lovelight Home Design

Award-winning Designers: 
2021 The Mississauga's Readers Choice for Interior Design, Diamond Award winner. 
2020 The Mississauga's Readers Choice for Interior Design, Diamond Award winner.

profile:
My name is Agnieszka  and I am the founder of ACA Design Studio. I have over 20 years of experience in the industry. My background is in Architecture (I have Bachelor's degree) and I have worked in Architecture/ Interior Design firms for 20 years on high end retail projects and commercial office spaces. My unique combination of skills helps me understand and visualize the area you want to renovate on your home and inspires me to create an architectural space which is visually stunning, functional and within your your budget.

Although I have a variety of experience in the field, I specialize in creating comfortable, functional kitchens and bathrooms for new homebuyers. 

FAQ:

Q. Do you provide Interior Design or Interior Decorating services.
A. ACA DESIGN STUDIO provides Interior Design services.

Q. What is the difference between Interior Designer and Interior Decorator?
A. Interior Decorators typically provide services dealing with specifying and buying furniture, carpeting, wallcovering, drapery and various decorative items such as lamps, pillows etc. You do not need a degree or a license to be an Interior Decorator. Interior Designers must obtain a degree in Interior Design or in Architecture and must have a license in order to practice. Interior Designers go thru a rigorous training and years of practice in various aspects of design and construction. Some of their experience includes but is not limited to: space planning, furniture and millwork design, concept design, construction supervision, hiring and coordination of work with architects and engineers, construction management and coordination, knowledge of the building codes, filing for permits and materials specifications. Interior Designers can prepare construction drawings which include: demolition, new construction of walls, electrical layout, ceiling lighting layout, new millwork and furniture. Interior Designers can help you with the construction and renovation of the interior of your home or a commercial space. 

Q. What is your education and Interior Design experience?
A. I have a Bachelor's Degree in Architecture from Pratt Institute in Brooklyn and I am licensed by CIDQ. My professional experience includes work on high end retail projects (Barney's New York stores, Versace Flagship store and residence in NYC, Polo Ralph Lauren boutiques), commercial projects (space planning and project management for an Insurance Company on Wall Street, renovation of office spaces in Toronto) and residential renovations for homes in Toronto.
If you would like to see the images of my previous work, please see my YOU TUBE video under PROJECTS tab- HOW I BECAME AN INTERIOR DESIGNER.

Q. How is ACA DESIGN STUDIO working during Covid lockdown.
A. As many of the Ontario areas are under strict lockdown or entering different stages of the reopening plan, ACA DESIGN STUDIO is now offering some services virtually thru ZOOM and FaceTime. There is a lot that can be accomplished virtually. Some projects will require that I take measurements on your space. If you are comfortable with me visiting your home, I would propose that I take measurements while you are in a separate space and after I am finished (and disinfected the items I touched) we meet outside to discuss the next steps or any concerns you have.

SERVICES which we offer DURING LOCKDOWN are:

Design Consultation- Virtual
Site Measurements
Renderings
Space Planning
Materials and FF&E research and procurement (Furniture, Furnishings and Equipment) by online search or showroom visit
Design Drawings
Construction Drawings

Q. What is the process of working on the project. 
A. Our first meeting is typically a Design Consultation which is now available (via Zoom) from the comfort of your home. During the consultation we will go over your expectations for the project, your lifestyle, preferences and likes, time line, budget as well as your inspiration images. I will then collect all that information and create a budget which is a fair representation of the work and send it to you for approval. 

If we decide to go ahead with the project, I would typically visit your home at this point (or space ) and take site measurements. During Covid-19, I would still prefer to take the measurements and photos myself (for accuracy reasons), so we can either arrange that I will do the work while you are in a separate room or we maintain a safe distance of 6 feet. I will be wearing a mask during the time I am in your home. 

After the initial meeting, and after we sign the agreement, there is still lots I can accomplish remotely. This includes work on renderings, concept package (including sourcing materials, finishes, equipment) and any design or construction drawings you need. We can also arrange to have samples sent to me and to you for review and approval.

As Toronto is under strict lockdown and construction work is still on HOLD, we will have to postpone on-site work until we move into the less strict color code. 

Q. Does ACA DESIGN STUDIO have a license to practice?
A. Yes ACA DESIGN STUDIO is certified by CIDQ (Council for Interior Design). https://www.cidq.org

Q. Are you insured?
A. ACA DESIGN STUDIO carries professional and liability insurance for all projects.

Q. What services do you  offer and how much do you typically charge for a project?
A. ACA DESIGN offers 3 packages of services: Design Consultation, Design Services and Design and Management Services. 
https://www.acadesignstudio.com/what-we-do
Please see the services page for more details.

DESIGN CONSULTATION:
Whether you are on a tight budget or simply just looking for some design ideas and want to pick our brains, this 90 minutes session will get you on the right path. During our time together, we will discuss what you love or don’t about your home, current design trends and which is the best one for your space as well as your goals.  This session can be focused on 1 space, or it can be a general design session to get your inspiration juices flowing while giving you an overall design direction for multiple spaces in your home.
 
Cost of Design Consultation is $350 for 90 minutes.

DESIGN SERVICES ONLY:
The Design Services package is a great choice if you are a self-motived individual with a vision. You may already have some inspiration ideas and have done your research, but you are tired of looking at websites and are still not closer to pulling the trigger. Maybe you are worried about making a mistake or you don’t know how to get started or you may be scared of getting stuck in the process. No matter the reason, we are happy to help. 

This package includes: Design Consultation, Site Measurements, Materials Selection, Design Development Drawings, Design Presentation and Project Review Meeting with the Contractor of your choice. Please click the link below to see the full description of what is included.

Cost of Design Services is based on hourly rate of $125/ hour and typically ranges between $6,650- $9,005. This estimate may vary depending on the size of the project.
Additional services can be purchased at $125/ hour rate.

DESIGN AND MANAGEMENT SERVICES:
The Design and Project Management package is a great choice if you are either short on time or you just are not confident how to go about finding a reliable contractor and managing the renovation process. You may be worried and feel overwhelmed about all the details which need to be coordinated between the design drawings and construction trades. You may also be worried about making a mistake and getting stuck in the process. We understand the process can feel overwhelming, and we are happy to help.  

This package includes: Design Consultation, Site Measurements, Materials Selection, Design Development Drawings, Construction Drawings, Selection of Contractor and Millworker, Site Visits, Supervision of Millwork Installation, Schedule and Budget Meeting, Punch List and Close Out.

Cost of Design and Management Services is based on hourly rate of $125/ hour, and typically ranges between $12,500- $17,750. This estimate may vary depending on the size of the project.
Additional services can be purchased at $125/ hour rate.
ACA DESIGN offers 3 packages of services: Design Consultation, Design Services and Design and Management Services. Please see our website for more details.

Q. How does ACA DESIGN STUDIO compare with other Interior Design firms?
A. Agnieszka Chromicz is the founder of ACA DESIGN STUDIO. She hold a Bachelor of Architecture Degree from the prestigious Pratt Institute in New York. Her interest in design has been a driving aspect in all her ventures.  She got her first taste for high-end retail design work as a Junior Designer at MSM Architects in NYC, where she worked on Gianni Versace’s flagship store in Manhattan. With a subsequent 4-year stay at American International Group on Wall Street,  she added project management and space planning skills to her list.  

Agnieszka earned a Masters Degree in Design and Technology at Parsons School of Design in 2001. She returned to work as an Architectural Designer, first for Polo Ralph Lauren and later for Jeffrey Hutchison Associates. At JHA, she spearheaded millwork development and production for Barney's New York flagship retail stores in the Las Vegas Palazzo, San Francisco, Boston and Chicago locations.  

In 2011, Agnieszka relocated to Toronto, where she joined internationally renowned entertainment design company Forrec Ltd. As Senior Interior Designer, she led teams working on theme parks, retail complexes and resort projects in China and Saudi Arabia.  

in 2016, Agnieszka opened a small Interior Design Firm with a renovation of a converted peanut factory loft and then with several office renovations in downtown Toronto.

Drawing on her background in diversified fields and applications, Agnieszka uses the design process to transform spaces and create an inspiring experience. Her passion for developing and delivering the best vision for the project, makes her an exceptionally valuable partner on innovative design projects.

Please reach out to us if you would like to get to know us better or if you have any other questions. 
We will be happy to hear from you. 

Or if you prefer to remain incognito, please visit our Website for more information.
